everal fish glide through blue-green water over a textured coral or rocky seabed. Dark fish pass across the foreground, and a lighter silver fish moves through the center, its body catching the light as it swims.\n\nA relaxed couple lies close together on a striped beach towel. The woman, in a colorful bikini top, smiles with her head near the man’s shoulder; he lies beside her, also relaxed. Sunlight casts striped shadows across them. At the bottom of the screen, white text reads, “Includes hotel and air fare.”\n\nA snorkeler emerges from the ocean, facing forward. The person wears a dark mask and snorkel, with water streaming heavily over the face and shoulders. The sea and pale blue sky fill the background as the water splashes up around the swimmer.\n\nAt sunset, two silhouetted adults walk side by side along the edge of the beach. The ocean glitters with orange reflections, palm trees line the shore in the distance, and their legs and reflections are visible in the wet sand. One figure carries something low at their side, and the pair lean close together as they walk.\n\nThe woman in the red-orange swimsuit returns, now reclining on a beach towel or lounge surface under her wide straw hat. She drinks through a straw from a coconut decorated with a large pink flower. The sandy beach and water are softly visible behind her. She pauses and looks forward while still holding the coconut, her white bracelet visible on one wrist.\n\nThe image then blends into an American Airlines airplane in flight. The silver fuselage fills the view, with the large red “American” lettering along the side and red, white, and blue striping beneath the windows. The landing gear is down, and engine pods are visible under the wing as the plane angles upward against a pale sky. As more of the aircraft comes into view, the tail shows the “AA” marking.\n\nThe final image places the airplane in the sky with a large promotional title beneath it. On-screen text reads “American’s Caribbean,” “$399,” and “Includes hotel and airfare.” Smaller text at the bottom says, “Call your travel agent for details and restrictions.”",
